Node.Notes: Precise meaning unknown. Parallelism and apparent guesses from ancient versions suggest something like oppressors/persecutors/captors.
Apparently carries over "ask us" from first part. Meaning uncertain. Could be ask us to be happy/to make them happy/to sing a happy song.

Uncertain. Different proposals given. LXX has "let my right hand be forgotten." Some change "forget" to "wither." Probably go with idea of forgotting how to play the harp and so "my my right hand forget [its skill]."
Apparently means "may I never be able to sing again."
Uncertain. Many change to active participle "devastator." If passive participle in text correct, then perhaps "doomed to be destroyed."
